Share of current countries that have had a woman as chief executive since 1789.
Note: The chief executive is the head of government (such as Germany's Angela Merkel) or the head of state (such as Argentina's Cristina
Fernndez de Kirchner), whoever has more power. Democracies as identified by V-Dem's 'Regimes of the World' classification.
